Geralyn R. Breig, Former Avon and Godiva Exec, Appointed to Welch’s Board of Directors | Business Wire


























































Geralyn R. Breig, Former Avon and Godiva Exec, Appointed to Welch’s 
      Board of Directors




New Director Brings Profit Growth Expertise to the Family-Farmer 
      Owned Cooperative






February 19, 2013 08:00 AM Eastern Standard Time



CONCORD, Mass.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Welch’s, 
      a family-farmer owned cooperative and the leading marketer of Concord 
      and Niagara grape-based products, announces the appointment of Geralyn 
      R. Breig to its Board of Directors. As one of five external directors, 
      Breig will use her extensive consumer products industry expertise, as 
      well as her experience driving business growth, to guide Welch’s short- 
      and long-term goals.
    


      “Geralyn has a proven record for growing businesses and delivering 
      financial results,” said Joseph Falcone, Chairman of the Welch’s Board, 
      and President of National Grape Cooperative Inc. “We’re looking forward 
      to gaining Geralyn’s perspective on driving further results for our 
      family-farmer owners.”
    

      A seasoned executive with 29 years of consumer products industry 
      experience, Breig is currently a board director with 1-800-Flowers.com. 
      She previously served as President of Avon North America & General 
      Manager Avon USA, the cosmetics, apparel and gift retailer. Breig led 
      Avon’s North American business recovery strategy, including increasing 
      profit and significantly reducing costs. Before Avon, Breig spent 10 
      years with the Campbell Soup Company’s Godiva and Pepperidge Farm 
      brands. As Godiva President, she transformed the brand by creating a new 
      retail concept and global store design. While a Pepperidge Farm Vice 
      President, she developed a strategic plan that doubled profits and grew 
      revenue. Prior to that, she spent several years with Kraft and Procter & 
      Gamble.
    

      “Welch’s is renowned as a trusted, family-oriented brand,” says Breig. 
      “I’m looking forward to working in the consumer manufacturing arena 
      again, and helping the Board drive growth for this iconic brand.”
    

      Breig received her B.S. in Economics from the Wharton School, University 
      of Pennsylvania.
    

About Welch’s


      Headquartered in Concord, Massachusetts, Welch’s is the processing and 
      marketing subsidiary of National Grape Cooperative. Welch’s is owned by 
      this cooperative of more than 
      1,000 family farmers across America and in Ontario, Canada, who grow 
      the delicious and inherently healthy Concord grape used in Welch’s 
      juices and other grape-based products. Welch’s is committed to research 
      and development that will meet the growing demand for products 
      addressing consumers’ health and nutrition needs. Welch’s products are 
      sold throughout the United States and in approximately 50 countries 
      globally. Welch’s is an Equal Opportunity Employer- 
      Minorities/Female/Disabled/Veterans. For more information, visit 
      welchs.com.
    


Contacts

      For Welch’sMary Thibault, 202-419-3260Mary.thibault@porternovelli.com













